# Load the datasets
customers_df = pd.read_csv('customers.csv', sep='\t')
sales_df = pd.read_csv('sales.csv')
store_df = pd.read_csv('store.csv')
season_trends_df = pd.read_csv('seasonshoppingtrends.csv')

Step 1: Clean Data¶

In [3]:
# Handle missing values and duplicates in all datasets
def clean_data(df):
    # Drop duplicates
    df.drop_duplicates(inplace=True)
    # Fill missing numeric values with 0
    df.fillna(0, inplace=True)
    return df

customers_df = clean_data(customers_df)
sales_df = clean_data(sales_df)
store_df = clean_data(store_df)
season_trends_df = clean_data(season_trends_df)

Step 2: Normalize Fields¶

In [4]:
# Convert date formats in customer and sales datasets
customers_df['Dt_Customer'] = pd.to_datetime(customers_df['Dt_Customer'], format='%d-%m-%Y')
sales_df['Date'] = pd.to_datetime(sales_df['Date'], format='%m/%d/%Y')

# Normalize categorical columns
customers_df['Education'] = customers_df['Education'].str.strip().str.title()
customers_df['Marital_Status'] = customers_df['Marital_Status'].str.strip().str.title()

Step 3: Feature Engineering¶

In [5]:
# Ensure columns are numeric
season_trends_df['Purchase Amount (USD)'] = pd.to_numeric(season_trends_df['Purchase Amount (USD)'], errors='coerce')
season_trends_df['Size'] = pd.to_numeric(season_trends_df['Size'], errors='coerce')

# Handle missing or invalid values after conversion
season_trends_df['Purchase Amount (USD)'].fillna(0, inplace=True)
season_trends_df['Size'].replace(0, np.nan, inplace=True)  # Avoid division by zero
season_trends_df['Size'].fillna(season_trends_df['Size'].mean(), inplace=True)  # Replace missing sizes with mean

# External Factors: Create variables for holiday boosts and weather conditions
# Adding a column to flag weekends
sales_df['Date'] = pd.to_datetime(sales_df['Date'], errors='coerce')  # Ensure Date is in datetime format
sales_df['Is_Weekend'] = sales_df['Date'].dt.weekday.isin([5, 6])

# Customer Metrics: Calculate total spend and repeat purchases
customers_df['Total_Spend'] = customers_df[['MntWines', 'MntFruits', 'MntMeatProducts', 
                                            'MntFishProducts', 'MntSweetProducts', 'MntGoldProds']].sum(axis=1)
customers_df['Repeat_Purchases'] = customers_df[['NumDealsPurchases', 'NumWebPurchases', 
                                                 'NumCatalogPurchases', 'NumStorePurchases']].sum(axis=1)

# Store Metrics: Sales per square foot and category performance
season_trends_df['Sales_Per_Square_Foot'] = season_trends_df['Purchase Amount (USD)'] / season_trends_df['Size']

# Save processed data to files
customers_df.to_csv('cleaned_customers.csv', index=False)
sales_df.to_csv('cleaned_sales.csv', index=False)
store_df.to_csv('cleaned_store.csv', index=False)
season_trends_df.to_csv('cleaned_season_trends.csv', index=False)

# Linear Regression: Predict Total Spending
X = customers_df[['Income', 'Recency', 'Repeat_Purchases']]
y = customers_df['Total_Spend']

# Add constant for statsmodels
X_sm = sm.add_constant(X)
model = sm.OLS(y, X_sm).fit()
print(model.summary())

# Select features for clustering
clustering_features = customers_df[['Total_Spend', 'Repeat_Purchases', 'Recency']]
scaler = StandardScaler()
scaled_features = scaler.fit_transform(clustering_features)

In [16]:
# K-Means Clustering
wcss = []
for i in range(1, 11):
    kmeans = KMeans(n_clusters=i, random_state=42)
    kmeans.fit(scaled_features)
    wcss.append(kmeans.inertia_)

# Elbow Method to find optimal clusters
plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
plt.plot(range(1, 11), wcss, marker='o', linestyle='--')
plt.title('Elbow Method', fontsize=16)
plt.xlabel('Number of Clusters', fontsize=12)
plt.ylabel('WCSS', fontsize=12)
plt.show()

Apply K-Means with optimal clusters (k=4)¶

In [17]:
kmeans = KMeans(n_clusters=4, random_state=42)
clusters = kmeans.fit_predict(scaled_features)
customers_df['Cluster'] = clusters

# Visualize Clusters
plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
sns.scatterplot(x=customers_df['Total_Spend'], y=customers_df['Repeat_Purchases'], 
                hue=customers_df['Cluster'], palette='viridis', s=100)
plt.title('Customer Segments Based on Spending and Purchases', fontsize=16)
plt.xlabel('Total Spending', fontsize=12)
plt.ylabel('Repeat Purchases', fontsize=12)
plt.legend(title='Cluster')
plt.show()
